name: Mossop the goblin witch
description:
Mossop is a grumpy gobin witch, who lived amongst the rocks, moss and roots of a nearby waterfall. She has mossy hair and a grumpy expression. I found her and her friend Murple scrambling around and brought them home. They're both looking for a nice, new and unusual home to live in.

She can stand, hang, and carry things in he arms. She is made from recycled wire, polymer clay and hand-painted.

name: Murple the Goblin witch
description:
Muple is a grumpy gobin witch, who lived amongst the rocks, moss and roots of a nearby waterfall. She has fluffy purpe hair and a lovely expression. I found her and Mossop, her grumpy fiend, out looking for acorns in the cold. They're both looking for a nice, new and unusual home to live in.

She can stands only 7cm tall, and can hang, and carry things in he arms. She is carefully made from recycled wire, polymer clay and hand-painted.

name: Gilbert the Goblin
description:
This fuzzy little fellow is Gilbert, a very rare goblin with his furry winter coat. This curious little creature loves to be warm, and is looking for a magical new home. 

Gilbert is not a toy. He's a unique creation, standing only 6cm tall and delicately hand-sculpted and hand-painted.
